net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc

Class DirContextSource.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.michaelo.dirctxsrc.DirContextSource.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    DirContextSource

    public static final class DirContextSource.Builder
extends Object
    A builder to construct a DirContextSource with a fluent interface.

    Notes:

    1. This class is not thread-safe. Configure the builder in your main thread, build the object and pass it on to your forked threads.
    2. An IllegalStateException is thrown if a property is modified after this builder has already been used to build a DirContextSource, simply create a new builder in this case.
    3. All passed arrays will be defensively copied and null/empty values will be skipped except when all elements are invalid, an exception will be raised.

        public Builder(String... urls)
        Constructs a new builder for DirContextSource with anonymous authentication.

        Note: The default context factory com.sun.jndi.ldap.LdapCtxFactory will iterate through all URLs/servers until the first one is reachable/available.

        Parameters:
        urls - The URL(s) of a directory server. It/they may contain root DNs.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if urls is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if urls is empty

        public DirContextSource.Builder qop(String... qop)
        Sets the quality of protection in preference order with which the connection to the directory server is secured. The first negotiated quality is used. Valid values are auth, auth-int, and auth-conf. This only works with SASL mechanisms which support this feature, e.g., Digest MD5 or GSS-API. See here for details.
        Parameters:
